Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive findings report.

## Summary of Findings

Based on my thorough exploration of the Crevia MVP codebase, here are the requested findings:

---

### 1. WHERE ACCEPTED APPLICATIONS ARE SHOWN IN CREVIACONNECT

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/components/crevia-connect/shared/CampaignApplicationsDialog.tsx`**
- **Line 102:** Accepted applications are filtered: `const acceptedApplications = applications.filter(app => app.status === "accepted");`
- **Line 118:** Tab trigger shows count: `<TabsTrigger value="accepted">Accepted ({acceptedApplications.length})</TabsTrigger>`
- **Lines 195-209:** Accepted applications tab content displays applications via `AcceptedApplicationCard` component
- **Lines 253-316:** `AcceptedApplicationCard` component renders individual accepted application cards with:
  - Creator name and acceptance date (lines 284-289)
  - Total price/proposed_price (line 300)
  - Escrow status badge showing payment phases (lines 291-294)
  - "View Workspace" action button (line 308)

**For Brand side (Campaign manager):**
- **File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/components/crevia-connect/shared/FundEscrowDialog.tsx`**
  - **Lines 175-247:** Shows accepted application funding and payment details
  - **Line 197:** Displays creator name
  - **Line 51-53:** Shows proposed_price breakdown into 50/50 escrow payments

**For Creator side (after accepting):**
- **File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/components/crevia-connect/creator/MyCampaignsTab.tsx`**
  - **Line 147:** Filters active applications: `const activeApplications = applications.filter(app => app.status === "accepted");`
  - **Line 174:** Displays count in tab: `<TabsTrigger value="active">Active ({activeApplications.length})</TabsTrigger>`

---

### 2. CREATE CONTRACT DIALOG (Canvas Creator)

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/components/studio/CreateContractDialog.tsx`**

**Props (Lines 15-22):**
```typescript
interface CreateContractDialogProps {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
  editingContract?: any;
  onSuccess: () => void;
  onCreated?: (id: string) => void;
  kiraContext?: Record<string, unknown> | null;
}
```

**Fields Supported (Lines 54-61):**
- `title` - Auto-generated as "Canvas – {date}" if not provided
- `client_name` - Required field
- `client_email` - Optional
- `content` - The contract/canvas text content (main editor)
- `contract_type` - Set to "custom"
- `user_id` - Set from session

**How it's Opened/Triggered (Examples):**
- **ContractsTab.tsx Line 652:** `<CreateContractDialog open={createDialogOpen || !!editingContract} onOpenChange={(open) => { ... }} editingContract={editingContract} />`
- **WorkspaceActionVault.tsx Lines 229, 240:** Button clicks trigger `setCreateContractOpen(true)`
- **Kira.tsx Line 65:** Imported and used similarly

**Pre-filling Support (Lines 36-45):**
- Supports `kiraContext` prop for pre-filling content from Kira
- `editingContract` prop for editing existing contracts
- Limited pre-fill: only `content` from kiraContext is used (line 41)
- **Currently lacks:** Pre-filling from query params or application data

**Data Persistence (Lines 64-82):**
- Uses Supabase table: `canvases` (not the traditional `contracts` table in types.ts)
- Insert operation: `supabase.from("canvases").insert(contractData).select("id").single()`
- Callback: `onCreated?.(created.id)` returns the created ID

---

### 3. CONTRACTSTAB (Canvas Manager)

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/components/studio/ContractsTab.tsx`**

**How CreateContractDialog is invoked:**
- **Line 337-349:** Button click opens dialog with limit check
  ```typescript
  onClick={async () => {
    if (isFree) {
      const { count } = await supabase.from("canvases").select("*", { count: "exact", head: true });
      if ((count || 0) >= limits.canvasesPerMonth) { toast.error(...); return; }
    }
    setCreateDialogOpen(true);
  }}
  ```
- **Line 651-659:** Dialog passed `open={createDialogOpen || !!editingContract}` with `editingContract` state

**Dialog Integration (Lines 651-659):**
```tsx
<CreateContractDialog
  open={createDialogOpen || !!editingContract}
  onOpenChange={(open) => {
    setCreateDialogOpen(open);
    if (!open) setEditingContract(null);
  }}
  editingContract={editingContract}
  onSuccess={fetchContracts}
/>
```

---

### 4. ROUTING FOR STUDIO/CANVAS

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/App.tsx`**
- **Line 166:** `/crevia-studio` opens the Studio page (protected route)
  ```typescript
  <Route path="/crevia-studio" element={<ProtectedRoute><AppLayout><CreviaStudio /></AppLayout></ProtectedRoute>} />
  ```

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/pages/CreviaStudio.tsx`**
- **Lines 14-29:** Studio tabs controlled by URL param: `tab=contracts`
- **Line 164:** Canvas (Contracts) tab opened when `activeTab === "contracts"`
- Full URL path: `/crevia-studio?tab=contracts`

---

### 5. APPLICATION DATA SHAPE (Accepted Applications)

**File: `/home/antonypeter/Projects/crevia/creviamvp/src/integrations/supabase/types.ts`**

**campaign_applications table (Lines 184-241):**
```typescript
Row {
  id: string;
  campaign_id: string;
  creator_id: string;
  status: "pending" | "accepted" | "rejected" | "completed";
  proposed_price: number | null;
  proposal: string | null;
  ai_match_score: number | null;
  created_at: string | null;
  updated_at: string | null;
}
```

**Joined campaign data from campaigns table (Lines 305-375):**
```typescript
Row {
  title: string;           // Campaign title
  budget: number | null;
  description: string | null;
  deliverables: string[] | null;
  brand_id: string;        // Campaign creator (Brand)
  deadline: string | null;
  platforms: string[] | null;
  industry: string | null;
  requirements: string | null;
}
```

**Creator profile data (via JOIN with profiles + creator_profiles):**
- From profiles table: `display_name`, `handle`, `email`, `avatar_url`
- From creator_profiles table: `follower_count`, `engagement_rate`, `creator_types`, `portfolio_url`, `social_links`

**How applications are queried (CampaignApplicationsDialog.tsx Lines 31-40):**
```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from("campaign_applications")
  .select("*, creator_profiles(*, profiles(*))")
  .eq("campaign_id", campaign.id)
  .order("created_at", { ascending: false });
```

**Key fields on accepted application:**
- `proposed_price` - The price creator proposed (line 160 in CampaignApplicationsDialog)
- `creator_id` - Links to creator
